cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with security and privacy issues in vehicular ad-hoc networks (VANETs) and proposes a blockchain-based anonymous reputation system (BARS) for trust management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed system, which involves distributed trust management and efficient certificate and revocation transparency, indicating that it could also fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The design of the trust model and experiments conducted to evaluate the system suggest that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
